cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with a mobile edge computing problem that involves communication between mobile users and computing nodes at the network edge. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the fundamental limits of communication and information processing. The paper also involves wireless communication, which suggests cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as another likely category. The problem of offloading computation tasks to edge nodes and optimizing the load of computation suggests cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as possible categories. Finally, the use of coded computations and communication messages suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) as a possible category.
